data.title: Movies and TV Shows
data.meta_description: Jenny Wright's filmography, sorted by online popularity. Learn more about the television and films they've appeared in.
data.text:
St. Elmo's Fire

as Felicia • # 854 most popular movie

St. Elmo's Fire is a 1985 American coming-of-age film that follows a group of recent graduates from Georgetown University as they navigate the challenges of adulthood, relationships, and career aspirations.

Young Guns II

as Jane Greathouse • # 1,724 most popular movie

Young Guns II is a 1990 American Western action film and a sequel to Young Guns (1988), starring Emilio Estevez, Kiefer Sutherland, Lou Diamond Phillips, and Christian Slater. The movie follows Billy the Kid's escape to Old Mexico while pursued by government agents led by Pat Garrett.

Pink Floyd: The Wall

as American Groupie • # 2,172 most popular movie

Pink Floyd: The Wall is a surrealistic musical drama film that follows a rock star named Pink as he spirals into madness while grappling with isolation.

The Lawnmower Man

as Marnie Burke • # 2,270 most popular movie

The Lawnmower Man is a 1992 science fiction horror film about a intellectually disabled gardener who becomes a genius following scientific experiments involving computer technology.

The World According to Garp

as Cushie • # 2,694 most popular movie

The World According to Garp is a 1982 American comedy-drama film starring Robin Williams, based on the novel by John Irving.

Near Dark

as Mae • # 2,859 most popular movie

Near Dark is a 1987 American neo-Western horror film about a young man who joins a family of nomadic American vampires after being bitten by a drifter.

The Executioner's Song

as April Baker • # 5,697 most popular movie

The Executioner's Song is a 1982 American made-for-television biographical crime drama film based on Norman Mailer's novel. It follows the story of Gary Gilmore's struggle to rebuild his life after serving time in prison, culminating in a series of tragic events.

The Wild Life

as Eileen • # 6,017 most popular movie

The Wild Life is an 1984 American coming-of-age comedy-drama film about the lives of three teenagers in Los Angeles, featuring a mix of rebellious antics and romantic entanglements.

The Chocolate War

as Lisa • # 6,971 most popular movie

The Chocolate War is a drama film that delves into the hierarchical structure of a Catholic boys' boarding school, focusing on a new student's rebellion against the established norms by refusing to sell chocolates.

A Shock to the System

as Melanie O'Conner • # 6,991 most popular movie

A Shock to the System is a 1990 American black comedy film featuring Michael Caine as Graham Marshall, an advertising executive who takes drastic measures when passed over for a promotion.

Queens Logic

as Asha • # 7,583 most popular movie

Queens Logic is a 1991 American ensemble coming-of-age comedy-drama film featuring a group of working-class childhood friends from Astoria, Queens, navigating adulthood and relationships.
